{
  "info": {
    "name": "DMV Motor API",
    "_postman_id": "dmv-motor-api-collection",
    "description": "DMV Motor backend (Spring Boot) API collection.\n\n## Auth flows\n- **prod env**: run `Auth & Setup → Login (refresh Firebase ID token)` first — its test script writes `idToken` into the collection variable. All authenticated requests inherit Bearer auth via `{{idToken}}`.\n- **local env**: `idToken` is preset to `1` (StubFirebaseVerifier matches `Bearer <numericUserId>` in dev/test). No login needed. Make sure a user with id=1 exists in the local DB; otherwise change `idToken` to a valid id.\n\n## Captured variables\nThese are written by test scripts as you exercise the flow:\n- `sessionId` — set by `Practice → Start session`\n- `questionId`, `variantId` — set by `Practice → Start session` (the first question returned)\n- `mockAttemptId` — set by `Mock Exam → Start attempt`\n- `reviewTaskId` — set by `Review → Get pack` (first task)\n\nDownstream requests reference them, so once you start a flow the rest just work.\n\n## Schema reference\n`docs/development/api-contract.md`\n",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      { "key": "token", "value": "{{idToken}}", "type": "string" }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "", "type": "default", "description": "Override per environment (local / prod)" },
    { "key": "firebaseApiKey", "value": "AIzaSyC7udEaD0FWMiz91N2pvmLppR4jGG3qhSU", "type": "default", "description": "Web API key from Firebase project (dmv-motor-prod). Public client key, safe to ship." },
    { "key": "firebaseEmail", "value": "", "type": "default" },
    { "key": "firebasePassword", "value": "", "type": "secret" },
    { "key": "idToken", "value": "", "type": "default", "description": "Firebase ID token. prod: filled by Login script. local: preset to '1' by env (stub)." },
    { "key": "sessionId", "value": "", "type": "default" },
    { "key": "questionId", "value": "", "type": "default" },
    { "key": "variantId", "value": "", "type": "default" },
    { "key": "mockAttemptId", "value": "", "type": "default" },
    { "key": "reviewTaskId", "value": "", "type": "default" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth & Setup",
      "description": "Run Login first when on prod env. Local env sets idToken=1 directly.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login (refresh Firebase ID token)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{firebaseEmail}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{firebasePassword}}\",\n  \"returnSecureToken\": true\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://identitytoolkit.googleapis.com/v1/accounts:signInWithPassword?key={{firebaseApiKey}}",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": [ "identitytoolkit", "googleapis", "com" ],
              "path": [ "v1", "accounts:signInWithPassword" ],
              "query": [ { "key": "key", "value": "{{firebaseApiKey}}" } ]
            },
            "description": "Exchanges email+password for a real Firebase ID token. Stores it in the `idToken` collection variable so downstream Bearer-auth requests just work."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.idToken) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('idToken', json.idToken);",
                  "    console.log('idToken stored (' + json.idToken.length + ' chars), localId=' + json.localId);",
                  "} else {",
                  "    console.error('No idToken in response:', json);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
